snippet: LEAD: Three days after Californians voted for a sweeping rollback in insurance rates, insurance agents and state officials say people are paying higher premiums for automobile coverage than before, at least for the time being....
lead_paragraph: LEAD: Three days after Californians voted for a sweeping rollback in insurance rates, insurance agents and state officials say people are paying higher premiums for automobile coverage than before, at least for the time being.

headline.main: Cost of Auto Insurance Increases in California

byline.original: By ROBERT REINHOLD, Special to the New York Times
